From: Crystal Hart <crystalh@andersonkia.ca>
Sent: Friday, January 24, 2025 2:02 PM
To: claims <claims@canadageneral.ca>
Subject: Engine Replacement Request for 2019 Kia Soul (Contract #W-250303)
 
Good afternoon,

 

I am reaching out regarding our customer, Denise Dudgeon, contract #W-250303, and her 2019 Kia Soul, which requires an engine replacement.

 

The vehicle arrived with audible engine noise, and we followed the Kia flow chart in relation to the active engine campaign.

 

KTAC verified that the noise is not related to crank rod bearing failure but is coming from the pistons due to scored cylinder walls. We scoped the cylinders and found scoring on the cylinder walls.

 

As per the diagnosis, we followed the Kia TSB (ENG03202107) and initiated K-TAC case #151346. KTAC's assessment indicated that while the noise in the provided video appears to be caused by piston slap, the engine has not failed according to the engine campaign guidelines.

 

I have attached the technician notes and photos of the cylinders for consideration

 

Please let me know if you need any additional information.

 

Thank You,

Craig A
notes.content:
From: Crystal Hart
Sent: Friday, January 24, 2025 2:02 PM
To: claims
Subject: Engine Replacement Request for 2019 Kia Soul (Contract #W-250303)

Good afternoon,



I am reaching out regarding our customer, Denise Dudgeon, contract #W-250303, and her 2019 Kia Soul, which requires an engine replacement.



The vehicle arrived with audible engine noise, and we followed the Kia flow chart in relation to the active engine campaign.



KTAC verified that the noise is not related to crank rod bearing failure but is coming from the pistons due to scored cylinder walls. We scoped the cylinders and found scoring on the cylinder walls.



As per the diagnosis, we followed the Kia TSB (ENG03202107) and initiated K-TAC case #151346. KTAC's assessment indicated that while the noise in the provided video appears to be caused by piston slap, the engine has not failed according to the engine campaign guidelines.



I have attached the technician notes and photos of the cylinders for consideration



Please let me know if you need any additional information.



Thank You,

Craig A
